article.headline: Washington 74, Cal St.-Fullerton 72
article.story: SEATTLE -- C.J. Wilcox made a pair of free throws with 3.6 seconds left to help give the Washington Huskies a comeback 74-72 victory over Cal-State Fullerton on Sunday night. Wilcox, who had a team-high 21 points, was fouled by Alex Harris, just after Harris made a 3-pointer from the right baseline to tie the game at 72. Husky guard Andrew Andrews also made three free throws inside of 22 seconds to keep the Huskies (4-3) ahead. He finished with 13 points. D. J. Seeley scored 24 points for the Titans (3-3). The Huskies trailed by 14 points at halftime, 43-29.
